      "span_text": "72 1␣,25(OH) 2 D 3 and its analogs inhibit the proliferation of some tumor-derived endothelial cells, inhibit the expression of vascular endothelial cell growth factor that induces angiogenesis in tumors, and suppress tenascin-C, which promotes growth, invasion, and angiogenesis during tumorigenesis. 73 Breast, colon, prostate, skin, lung, and a variety of other cell lines, when exposed to 1␣,25(OH) 2 D 3, showed marked inhibition of cellular growth and induction of terminal differentiation. Although vitamin D is not currently used as a chemotherapeutic agent, it shows promise for drug development in the treatment of certain cancers."
